<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
  <title>Search By Squawk</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/styles.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../../public/styles/styles.css" />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Audiowide|Ibarra+Real+Nova&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

</head>

<body>

  <header>
    <%- include ('../partials/header') %>
  </header>

  <nav>
    <%- include ('../partials/nav') %>
  </nav>

  <main id="squawkPage">
    <h2>Squawk Search</h2>

    <p>Squawk codes are assigned by air traffic control to uniquely identify aircraft. These four digit codes can be
      displayed on ground radars to help manage traffic in tight airspaces. Generally these codes just identify aircraft, but there are special codes to help air traffic controllers know about an aircraft's status as well.  List below are a few squawk codes you can
      search to see what is out there!</p>
    <ul>
      <li>1200 - Unassigned/Anonymous Aircraft</li>
      <li>7500 - Aircraft Hijacking</li>
      <li>7600 - Radio Failure</li>
      <li>7700 - In-flight Emergency</li>
    </ul>
    <form action="/results" method="GET">
      <fieldset>
        <legend>Search by Squawk</legend>
        <br>
        <input type="number" min="0" max="7777" size="6" name="squawk" required autofocus>
        <input type="hidden" name="searchType" value="squawkURL">
        <br>
        <br>
        <button class="button">Submit</button>
      </fieldset>
    </form>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <%- include ('../partials/footer') %>
  </footer>
  <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
  <script src="../../planeanimation.js"></script>
</body>



</html>